Use Cases

Start Game – User initializes a Tic-Tac-Toe board with size N×N.

Make a Move – A player places their symbol (X or O) on an available cell.

Check for Win/Draw – After every move, the system checks for a winning condition (vertical or horizontal only) or draw.

Notify Opponent – Once a player makes a move, the system sends an in-app notification to the other player.

End Game – System declares the winner or announces a draw.
